REASONING: According to the CIA World Factbook's Real GDP per capita comparison for 2024, Singapore ranks #1 with $132,600 per capita, ahead of Luxembourg at #2 with $128,200

The Wikipedia page on nominal GDP per capita shows different rankings where Monaco leads with $256,581, Liechtenstein at $207,973, and Luxembourg at $140,941, with Singapore appearing lower in the nominal rankings
The discrepancy between rankings is due to different methodologies: the CIA uses PPP-adjusted figures while Wikipedia shows nominal GDP per capita
Using the purchasing power parity (PPP) method which adjusts for cost of living differences, Singapore does rank as the highest
However, using nominal GDP per capita without PPP adjustments, Monaco and Luxembourg rank higher than Singapore
The claim's validity depends on which measurement methodology is used - PPP-adjusted vs nominal GDP per capita
